label.value: RNA absent from cell during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect during the meiotic cell cycle. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: normal RNA level during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during the meiotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of coenzyme Q10 measured in the cell is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of coenzyme Q10 measured in the cell is higher than normal.

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of Glc3Man9GlcNAc measured in a cell is higher than normal. Glc3Man9GlcNAc2 is an N-glycan that is involved in post-translational modification of proteins, and consists of a branched ten-membered mannooligosaccharide containing three D-glucose residues, nine D-mannosyl residues and two N-acetylglucosamine residues.

definition.value: Note that these terms treat Man(n)GlcNAc and Man(n)GlcNAc2 as equivalent. The reason is that the GlcNAc2 form is attached to N-linked glycoproteins, but the GlcNAc form is what is usually detected in experiments, following cleavage by endoglycosidase H. For the purposes of observing and interpreting phenotypes, the difference is not significant.

label.value: normal cell wall polysaccharide composition during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the levels and proportions of polysaccharides in the cell wall are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal cell wall morphology during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the size, shape, and structure of the cell wall are normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal termination of RNA polymerase III transcription

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the termination of RNA transcription RNA polymerase III from a DNA template is abnormal.

label.value: increased transcriptional readthrough at RNA polymerase III-transcribed genes

value.value: A phenotype in which a transcript synthesized on a DNA template by RNA polymerase III is longer than normal due to transcription beyond the normal termination site.

label.value: heterochromatin assembly beyond boundary element IRL

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled over a larger region near the silent mating-type cassette than normal, such that it extends beyond the IRL boundary element.

label.value: normal spatial extent of heterochromatin assembly to boundary element IRL

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled up to, but not beyond, the IRL boundary element in the silent mating-type cassette, as in wild type.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in silent mating-type cassettes occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at transposable element during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal at transposable elements.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 dimethylation at transposable element during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) at transposable elements.

label.value: increased spatial extent of heterochromatin assembly at protein coding gene

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled over a larger portion of the chromosome than normal in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: normal spatial extent of heterochromatin assembly at protein coding gene

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled over a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) portion of the chromosome in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: normal chromatin silencing at centromere otr1R

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at the right outer repeat region (otr1R) of the centromere is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: Note that the centromere outer repeat region corresponds to SO:0001799. Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: decreased chromatin silencing at centromere otr1R

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat regions is decreased at the right outer repeat region (otr1R) of the centromere.

definition.value: Note that the centromere outer repeat region corresponds to SO:0001799. Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at centromere otr1L

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat regions is increased at the left outer repeat region (otr1L) of the centromere.

definition.value: Note that the centromere outer repeat region corresponds to SO:0001799. Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. label.value: normal chromatin silencing at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromere inner repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of antisense RNA measured in a cell normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Antisense RNA is transcribed from the coding, rather than the template, strand of DNA.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased histone turnover at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone exchange occurs to a lower extent than normal at the silent mating-type cassette. Histone exchange is replacement, within chromatin, of resident histones or histone subunits with alternative, sometimes variant, histones or subunits.
decreased histone turnover at transposable element during vegetative growth

http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboI.value: decreased histone exchange at transposable element during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone exchange occurs to a lower extent than normal at transposable elements. Histone exchange is replacement, within chromatin, of resident histones or histone subunits with alternative, sometimes variant, histones or subunits.

A cell phenotype in which a protein that is normally dynamically localized to a specific place in the cell shows a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) temporal pattern of localization. For example, a protein may move to or from the location more or less frequently than normal.
